			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Tired of the same old zones, the same old raids and the same old people?
<br />

<br />
Then why not turn over a new leaf in your Everquest career and take this opportunity to join the House of Carnage, one of Firiona Vie's oldest guilds. We're currently holding an open recruitment period and we're inviting everyone to come to the Firiona Vie special rules server and start a new character.
<br />

<br />
We'll help you level up, give you some gear to get you on your way and instantly you'll become part of a fun, family environment where you'll be able to make new friends and experience a new side to Everquest.
<br />

<br />
We'll be monitoring all of our new applicants closely and those that show the ability to gain levels quickly, play their class well and have the potential to become great players and members of the guild will have their membership sollidified.
<br />

<br />
The House of Carnage aims to become one of the premier casual raiding guilds on Firiona Vie and we're particuarily interested in players from European time zones and the Eastern US.
<br />

<br />
If you're interested in taking up this fantastic opportunity to get a fresh start and add a new lease of life to Everquest then why not visit our website at <a href="http://hoc.eq.tripod.com" target="_blank">http://hoc.eq.tripod.com</a> for more information.
<br />

<br />
Alternatively you can just roll up a character on the Firiona Vie server and join the chat channel hoc:hoc (firiona.hoc:hoc if you're joining the channel on a different server). Once in game the officer's to contact are Fallor or Darqice.
<br />

<br />
Thanks and I look forward to seeing you in game!
<br />

<br />
Lord Fallor Manaribbon,
<br />
Guild Leader, The House of Carnage.
<br />

<br />

<br />
--- Information regarding Firiona Vie --
<br />
Firiona Vie's special rulest means, amongst other things that 99% of items can be traded and that only 1 character is allowed per account. Firiona Vie is the roleplaying preferred server and all players are advised that while on the server your actions do not interrupt or prohibit the roleplay of others. Having said that I'm sure you will find the FV community welcoming.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
